column5: These are great tips, thanks!
Sounds like you got ghosted. Your best bet is to leave her alone for at least a week or two. But sounds like it’s a lost cause already
Thanks!

This actually means a lot to me. I’m also an aspiring music artist and just like everything else in my life right now, it’s not going so well and not even my close friends support what I do. But this gives me hope, I keep going cause it’s what I love, but it gets so difficult sometimes. But I’ve made it this far, and your story gives me some hope, thank you for sharing.
Considering this, pretty sure this is gonna scare her off but I don’t wanna waste my time either.
That’s actually a pretty good idea, I game better in groups anyway, the dates are what I have to get better at.

That’s good man, a step in the right direction. Focus on yourself first. The first month of a break up is always hell, but things will get better, trust me. Enjoy the time you have to yourself, even if it does suck sometimes, you are in a unique point in your life that you will never experience again. Hope your days are getting better as well

I catch myself shaking my head when this happens like if there is a bug on my head, I always look crazy but it honestly hurts when this happens and I want to get it out of my head cause it’s so painful.

Was in this same position just a few months ago. Broke up with my gf, moved to a new place, it was fun for a bit but then became lonely. Now I’m moved back, surrounded by family and friends who barely even give a fuck. It’s the same no matter where you go

First time posting here, have to vent somewhere, the days have become fucking unbearable. This is the first time I’ve felt like there’s nothing left worth experiencing in this world, only thing keeping me going is my family but honestly, they cause me so much stress with having to take care of all of them that they aren’t really a relief for me. I was doing great 2 months ago, probably the happiest I’ve ever been, and maybe that’s why I’m feeling the way I am now. To finally have confidence in myself, to have security, to have money and be able to save, to travel, it’s all gone in a matter of weeks and I’m not even sure how I got there or how to get it back. Being back in the struggle sucks, this is what I’ve been trying to escape my entire life, only to be brought back into it. It feels like this is my place, where I’m suppose to be forever, and I’m tired of having to fight it every fucking time.

They dgaf dude, they have 100’s of people viewing that shit daily. If a girl wants you to notice it they will let you know. They’ll message your story, or mention something you guys have talked about in their own story.... a chick will let you know if they are interested in stuff like that.
Lmfao yup, learned this the hard way
